    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it really is. and it's not even like i'm being dramatic, it's just the reality of my body. it feels like i'm just waiting for a permission slip to finally be at peace. like, if there was a way to just... opt out without it being a \"tragedy,\" if death could just be seen as an act of mercy instead of something scary. do you think it's wrong to want that? to just want the hurting to be over for good?",
